PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1780600264
OL,3,C'Drowned' baby had dry hair, murder
OL,4,Ctrial hears
OL,6,FMr Wright said: "Shall we try again?
OL,7,FHis hair wasn't wet, was it?"
OL,9,FThe defendant replied: "No. Jay told
OL,10,Fme what had happened. I just remember
OL,11,Fhim saying, 'He was in his bath seat
OL,12,Fand then he wasn't'.
OL,14,F"I didn't think, 'A bath has not
OL,15,Fhappened. This is not right'."
OL,17,FMr Wright continued: "Dry hair. Towels
OL,18,Fon the floor, dry body. Wearing a
OL,19,Fnappy. Being told he had been in a
OL,20,Fbath seat."
OL,26,@nD@QOUoD@]O]qD@XOUvD@AOUwD@^O]yD@VOU|D@
OL,26,AKO]
