PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1780600264
OL,3,C'Drowned' baby had dry hair, murder
OL,4,Ctrial hears
OL,6,FThe defendant said: "When I entered
OL,7,Fthat house I was absolutely terrified,
OL,8,Fthat I entered a scene I did not
OL,9,Fexpect to see. I was shocked, I was
OL,10,Ftrying to help him and trying to get
OL,11,Fhim the medical attention he needed as
OL,12,Fsoon as I possibly could do."
OL,14,FThey rushed the child to hospital
OL,15,Fwhere medical staff noted the child
OL,16,Fdid not cough up water during an hour-
OL,17,Flong attempt at resuscitation.
OL,26,@nD@UOUtD@]O]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,396,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F395A1780600264
OL,3,C'Drowned' baby had dry hair, murder
OL,4,Ctrial hears
OL,6,FAnd a post-mortem examination later
OL,7,Fruled out drowning as a cause of death
OL,8,Fand found 40 external and internal
OL,9,Ftrauma injuries to the child's body,
OL,10,Fconsistent with "forcible penetration"
OL,11,Fand sexual abuse.
OL,13,FMr Wright suggested the two defendants
OL,14,Fhad "put your heads together" and were
OL,15,F"covering up for each other".
OL,17,FMcGowan-Fazakerley replied: "No. I
OL,18,Fwould never cover up over the safety
OL,19,Fof my child."
OL,26,@rD@QOUrD@fO]vD@EOUvD@]O]wD@AOUwD@\O]yD@
OL,26,A]OU{D@MO]
